data.body:
Tried integrating atom.io with Atomic Game Engine. Noticed an Issue when using the Atomic Game Engine Package

ERROR: Could not parse JSON data from *.atomic

The *.atomic project file doesn't get populated with:
{
   "version": 1,
   "project": {
      "version": "1.0.0"
   },
   "platforms": [
      "mac", "windows"
   ]
}
as in the example projects.

If code is triggered that throws an error, for example:

```
        if (input.getKeyDown(Atomic.KEY_SPACE)) 
        {
            throw "FOO";
        }
```

The editor crashes.

This occurs in any script with more than a few lines of code, the following component will recreate it (the error will be reported at line 12, instead of line 9):

// Atomic Component

var game = Atomic.game;
var ui = game.ui;
var root = ui.getRoot;

var uiStyle = game.cache.getResource("XMLFile", "UI/DefaultStyle.xml");
foo
function start() {

}

function update(timeStep) {

}
